Shortbread Cookies with Jam
  --LB in Middle Georgia (food.com)

1 c butter
2/3 c sugar
1/2 tsp almond extract (or vanilla)
2 c ap flour
1/2 c jam, for the centers

Cream butter and sugar. Beat in extract. Gradually blend in flour. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hr. Preheat oven to 350F. Roll into 1" balls and place 1" apart on ungreased cookie sheet. With the end of a wooden spoon make an indention in the ball and fill with jam. Bake for 14-18 min.


Notes: Any jams/jellies work, raspberry, apricot, apple, blackberry, blueberry, etc.

